A woman is set to appear in court next week for allegedly abducting an eight-month-old baby in Kraaifontein, Cape Town, Western Cape police said yesterday.Baby Lucas was found unharmed on Thursday, two days after he went missing. On Tuesday morning, his grandmother allowed a woman, who is known to them, to take the child to someone down the road. The woman never returned. Captain FC Van Wyk said a 37-year-old woman was arrested in Scottsdene on Friday morning. She&nbsp;is expected to&nbsp;appear in the Kuils River Magistrate&rsquo;s Court on Monday. News24